\begin_layout Standard
The package 
\series bold
Rd2roxygen
\series default
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Rd2roxygen"

\end_inset

 helps R package developers who used to write R documentation in the raw
 LaTeX-like commands but want to switch their documentation to 
\series bold
roxygen2
\series default
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "roxygen2"

\end_inset

, which is a convenient tool for developers, since we can write documentation
 as inline comments, e.g.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Chunk
<<roxygen-ex>>=
\end_layout

\begin_layout Chunk
## the source code of the function `parse_and_save`
\end_layout

\begin_layout Chunk
ex.file = system.file('examples','parse_and_save.R',package='Rd2roxygen')
\end_layout

\begin_layout Chunk
cat(readLines(ex.file), sep='
\backslash
n')
\end_layout

\begin_layout Chunk
@
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
With 
\series bold
roxygen2
\series default
 (typically using 
\emph on
roxygenize()
\emph default
), we can create the real Rd file from the above source code like this:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Chunk
<<rd-ex>>=
\end_layout

\begin_layout Chunk
